# Bolt Project Configuration

## Repository Connection
- **GitHub Repo**: milesmadeitfye-creator/Myghostev5
- **Branch**: main
- **Remote URL**: https://github.com/milesmadeitfye-creator/Myghostev5
## Build Configuration
- **Build Command**: `npm run build`
- **Output Directory**: `dist`
- **Framework**: Vite + React + TypeScript

## Deployment Workflow
1. Edit code in **Bolt** (this editor)
2. Click **Publish** → commits to `main` branch
3. **Netlify** automatically detects changes and deploys
4. Live at:
   - Primary: https://ghoste.one
   - Secondary: https://myghoste.netlify.app

## Important Notes
- ✅ Bolt is ONLY the editor
- ✅ Netlify handles ALL hosting and DNS
- ✅ NO custom domain settings in Bolt
- ✅ NO bolt.host deployments
- ✅ Changes push to GitHub → Netlify auto-deploys

## Environment Variables
Set these in **Netlify Dashboard** (NOT in Bolt):
- VITE_SUPABASE_URL
- VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
- SUPABASE_URL
- SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
- META_APP_ID
- META_APP_SECRET
- META_REDIRECT_URI
- STRIPE_SECRET_KEY
- STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET
- STRIPE_PRICE_PRO_MONTHLY

## Verification Checklist
✅ Repo linked to milesmadeitfye-creator/Myghoste
✅ Branch set to main
✅ Build command: npm run build
✅ Output directory: dist
✅ No conflicting domain settings in Bolt
✅ Netlify handles continuous deployment